For some reason, I love movies set in the snow.  Everything looks beautiful, but you know how dangerous that beauty can be.  This movie quickly gets into displaying the negative character traits, so one can decide who the baddies are.  Then they just as quickly start dying off.  This revenge plot twist can be figured out fairly quickly, but it is still exciting enough.  I was impressed with all of the acting and several folks did an excellent job.  All around enjoyable.

This movie was far better than I expected. Decent job on every front, with only minor issues throughout. Was sort of a modern take on "The Most Dangerous Game", with a bit more gore and a few plot holes.

The film has a fantastic set up, but falters a bit in the latter half.

Despite its flaws I was entertained. The acting, cinematography, score, and overall story was good, not groundbreaking or amazing, but better than most indie fare.

SPOILER WARNING!!!!
In fact, the ending was downright terrible, with plot holes and odd choices throughout. So much more could've been done but it seemed as though the writer(s) felt like they had to keep ramping the pace up only to jump the shark about halfway through. The "big twist" at the end was all too predictable.
This is one AWESOME THRILLER, it's a must see.
EXCELLENT MOVIE!!! Terrific cast, wonderful acting, super plot, and BEAUTIFUL scenery!!! Kept me on the edge of my seat all the way through the entire movie. SO GLAD I found this on here tonight!

Now the movie is okay to watch.  The plot is entertaining enough to keep your interest, but nothing very original.  There are plenty of summaries so I will not do this, but the movie's downfall in my opinion, is that very few of the characters are likable.  When something horrible happens to a character you are supposed to feel something and this is supposed to engage you more-- love, hate, anxiety, empathy, etc.  Instead you feel kind of ambiguous.  There are minor plot twists but not worth mentioning.

If you like the type of film where the characters are battling the elements, the wilderness, as well as hunting or being hunted, then you will probably take a favorable look to this.

Garbage movie ... but occasionally fun. The beginning tricks you into thinking it might be a quality film ... because some scenery bits are filmed with a drone, no doubt. But while the plot unfolds, there are many breaks in motivation and logic, leading to unrealistic action.

Kudos, though, for doing what so many big budget Hollywood movies don't do ... actually filming an outdoor movie outdoors, in the cold. That's why I give 3 stars, instead of 1.

I wasn't expecting much, but this was actually pretty good.  One of the characters was so annoying that it was almost to the point of being unrealistic (but then I ended up rooting for him to survive).  And the variety of unique characters was actually one of the movie's strong points.  I'd recommend it highly!

I liked the idea of the movie and being in the woods during winter time. There was enough action to keep me interested for a bit, when it came to the "gore" factor there wasn't a lot of that. There was a little violence sprinkled here and there throughout the movie but nothing to write home about or over the top. Overall a decent movie if you're looking for something half fun to watch. Ending was pretty much par for this type of movie about half way through you could figure out what's going on.

This was one of the worst movies I have ever seen. Terrible writing and ridiculous plot. The best scene is at the end when the credits finally rolled. Had some potential but was completely ruined by a bad script. Perhaps another good scene was when one of the characters throws a rock at the most annoying character. Too bad he didn't get knocked out for the rest of the film. Suffering from PTSD now after watching this. Tell everyone you meet to not watch this. You're welcome.
This movie was so bad and nonsensical, you will be talking about it the next day. Just bad. Plot holes and stupid dialogue. Save yourself. Keep moving.

I am giving 5 to balance out the unfair reviews here. OK so it's not the greatest film and the acting was tepid but it did have some plot twists and and it was not at all "predictable"  as one reviewer said.  It had enough to keep it interesting.  Not just a slasher and gore film.
